<TEXT>

Automobile sales in the United States down sharply

<TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2009-02-03">February 03, 2009</TIMEX3>

Sales of automobiles in the United States fell as much as 35% in <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2009-01">January</TIMEX3>, compared to <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="2008-01">the same month a year ago</TIMEX3>, as manufacturers reported their <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="2009-01">January</TIMEX3> sales.

Ford Motor Company sales dropped 42% <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE" value="2009-01">last month</TIMEX3> from <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DATE" value="2008">the previous year</TIMEX3>.

General Motors reported a 49% decline.

Chrysler was hardest hit among the domestically owned manufacturers with a plunge of 55%.

